Pages 139 through 145 in the annotated slide deck cover JCC.

I used JCC 2.12: http://lucene.apache.org/pylucene/jcc/


To compile ScalaUtils.scala:

scalac ScalaUtils.scala


To package the classes generated by the above compilation process into scala-utils.jar so that JCC can access them:

jar -cf scala-utils.jar ScalaUtils*.class


To create a Python package that provides access to the ScalaUtils library and install it:

python -m jcc.__main__ --package java.lang --include /path/to/scala-library.jar 
--jar scala-utils.jar  --python staircase --version 0.5 --build --install


